after she went to the school, right.

00:48:09.190 --> 00:48:14.350
After she went to that school
with children of all races,

00:48:14.350 --> 00:48:16.960
she went on to middle
school, high school,

00:48:16.960 --> 00:48:19.790
she went to college,
and she became a nurse.

00:48:19.790 --> 00:48:23.160
And she worked as a nurse for a
long time, for almost 30 years.

00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:27.080
But then her mother got sick,
and so she stopped working

00:48:27.080 --> 00:48:29.150
so she could take care
of her mother.

00:48:29.150 --> 00:48:31.730
And when her mother was very
sick, she said, you know,

00:48:31.730 --> 00:48:37.500
I'm so sad that no one knows
about our story and all the things

00:48:37.500 --> 00:48:39.150
that we did to make it

00:48:39.150 --> 00:48:41.600
so that children could
go to school together.

00:48:41.600 --> 00:48:44.460
So Sylvia decided she was not
going to work as a nurse anymore

00:48:44.460 --> 00:48:47.030
and that instead she was going
to start traveling and talking

00:48:47.030 --> 00:48:52.840
with people about this case so more
people would find out about it.

00:48:52.840 --> 00:48:56.610
And in that room were she
used to take care of her mom

00:48:56.610 --> 00:48:58.690
when she was sick, now
it's kind of her office.

00:48:58.690 --> 00:49:02.600
And she has all these awards
and all these different pictures

00:49:02.600 --> 00:49:06.370
and recognitions for her
effort, for her family's effort

00:49:06.370 --> 00:49:09.600
and for her effort so that more
people learn about this story

00:49:09.600 --> 00:49:13.470
and to talk about education
and equality.

